<br>
Lets see. Reasons I have heard that people think manaburn should be nerfed:<br>
<br>
1) Insta-kill ability in PvP. It's not fair for other characters because they don't have a fighting chance.<br>
<br>
Well, that's all good and true except for the fact that that wizard spent the better of 80+ levels getting owned by just about every other class in the game because his hands are already tied in PvP. However, if you don't want to give wizards an insta-kill ability make PC's immune to manaburn. Doesn't make much RP sense but then neither does making a level 2 mob immune to something that hits a level 60+ mob.<br>
<br>
2) Mobs like Sontalak shouldn't be taken down so quickly with so few people.<br>
<br>
Well, do you do math? Should have realized when this ability came out that it would only take x mb wizards to take out a mob with y hitpoints. That was going to happen and to not see that coming (and expect people not to do it) was foolish. Better solution is to make it so there is a delay to when someone can manaburn something after it has been hit once. Hell, even something as small as a 30 second delay will prevent it from happening.<br>
<br>
3) People farm the Kunark dragons with it.<br>
<br>
By all accounts this happens anyway. Nerf levels 51+ if you want to stop this.<br>
<br>
This post, while being critical of VI, isn't meant to slam them. The point is there are much better, and fairer, ways to deal with these issues other than the path they chose. I plead to Verant, please reconsider this change before making it live.<br>
